## Niveles de test

### Unit
- Prueba una clase en aislamiento
- Sin base de datos, sin HTTP, sin filesystem
- Usa mocks/fakes para dependencias externas
- Objetivo: lógica de negocio pura (Services, Actions, LimitService, TokenService)

```php
// tests/Unit/Subscriptions/LimitServiceTest.php
test('returns plan limit when no override exists', function () {
    $plan = Plan::factory()->make(['limits_json' => ['max_members' => 10]]);
    $subscription = Subscription::factory()->make(['plan' => $plan, 'override_json' => null]);

    $result = (new LimitService)->getLimit($subscription, 'max_members');

    expect($result)->toBe(10);
});

test('override takes precedence over plan limit', function () {
    $plan = Plan::factory()->make(['limits_json' => ['max_members' => 10]]);
    $subscription = Subscription::factory()->make([
        'plan'          => $plan,
        'override_json' => ['max_members' => 50],
    ]);

    $result = (new LimitService)->getLimit($subscription, 'max_members');

    expect($result)->toBe(50);
});

test('returns -1 for unlimited plan', function () {
    $plan = Plan::factory()->make(['limits_json' => ['max_members' => -1]]);
    $subscription = Subscription::factory()->make(['plan' => $plan, 'override_json' => null]);

    expect((new LimitService)->getLimit($subscription, 'max_members'))->toBe(-1);
});
```

