### Feature
- Prueba un endpoint REST de extremo a extremo dentro del backend
- Usa DB (SQLite por defecto, PostgreSQL para ltree)
- Cubre autenticación, autorización y formato de respuesta

```php
// tests/Feature/Auth/LoginTest.php
test('login with valid credentials returns tokens', function () {
    $user = User::factory()->create(['password' => bcrypt('secret')]);

    $this->postJson('/api/v1/auth/login', [
        'email'    => $user->email,
        'password' => 'secret',
    ])->assertOk()
      ->assertJsonStructure([
          'data' => ['access_token', 'refresh_token', 'expires_in'],
      ]);
});

test('login with wrong password returns error code', function () {
    $user = User::factory()->create();

    $this->postJson('/api/v1/auth/login', [
        'email'    => $user->email,
        'password' => 'wrong',
    ])->assertStatus(401)
      ->assertJson([
          'error' => ['code' => 'auth.invalid_credentials'],
      ]);
});

test('login with non-existent email returns same error code', function () {
    $this->postJson('/api/v1/auth/login', [
        'email'    => 'ghost@example.com',
        'password' => 'secret',
    ])->assertStatus(401)
      ->assertJson([
          'error' => ['code' => 'auth.invalid_credentials'],
      ]);
    // Mismo código intencionalmente — no revelar si el email existe
});
```

