### Base exception class

```php
// app/Exceptions/AppException.php
namespace App\Exceptions;

use RuntimeException;
use Throwable;

/**
 * Excepción base del sistema.
 *
 * Toda excepción de negocio debe extender esta clase.
 * Los controladores la capturan y delegan a ResponseFormatter::error()
 * para producir la respuesta JSON estándar con el código de error.
 *
 * El frontend usa error.code para resolver el mensaje i18n:
 *   errors.{code} → e.g. errors['workspace.depth_exceeded']
 *
 * @see ErrorCode           Para el catálogo completo de códigos
 * @see ResponseFormatter   Para el formato de respuesta de error
 */
abstract class AppException extends RuntimeException
{
    public function __construct(
        protected readonly ErrorCode $errorCode,
        protected readonly int       $httpStatus = 422,
        protected readonly array     $context    = [],
        ?Throwable                   $previous   = null,
    ) {
        parent::__construct($errorCode->value, $httpStatus, $previous);
    }

    public function getErrorCode(): ErrorCode { return $this->errorCode; }
    public function getHttpStatus(): int      { return $this->httpStatus; }
    public function getContext(): array       { return $this->context; }
}
```

### Excepciones concretas (una por caso de negocio)

```php
// app/Domain/Workspaces/Exceptions/WorkspaceDepthExceededException.php
class WorkspaceDepthExceededException extends AppException
{
    public function __construct(int $current, int $max)
    {
        parent::__construct(
            errorCode:  ErrorCode::WorkspaceDepthExceeded,
            httpStatus: 422,
            context:    ['current_depth' => $current, 'max_depth' => $max],
        );
    }
}

// app/Domain/Subscriptions/Exceptions/PlanLimitExceededException.php
class PlanLimitExceededException extends AppException
{
    public function __construct(string $metric)
    {
        parent::__construct(
            errorCode:  ErrorCode::PlanLimitExceeded,
            httpStatus: 422,
            context:    ['metric' => $metric],
        );
    }
}
```

**Respuesta REST resultante:**
```json
{
  "error": {
    "code": "workspace.depth_exceeded",
    "context": { "current_depth": 5, "max_depth": 3 }
  }
}
```

Los controladores atrapan sus propias `AppException` y delegan el formato a `ResponseFormatter::error($e)`.
Ver `docs/stages/02-backend-base.mdc` para la implementación de `ResponseFormatter`.

